== Altering Assets==
===Fixing Faulty Content===
All content is not treated equally. This prejudicial attitude is evinced by Trainz against the unwary by means of using the {{TR|T|trainz-build}} number to process data differently on reading it's data. Essentially, every older asset gets translated into a newer data model in Trainz internally. When the data can't be, or because the programmers choose to not ignore some data tag and field, errors are generated by the newer Trainz releases.
{{TrainzTip|
:''Editor's note: Some errors occur in later releases because the Trainz data model changed in the release.
* This many times avoidable'' 'Obsoleted by Program Changes' situation ''is the case now for some {{TR|ST|p=tags}} ''if content is upgraded'', but was very noticeable in Steam Locomotives brought forward into TC3 and TS2009's new data models (when they didn't work) and the parade of new errors messages continue with new levels of error checking at each release.}}
# {{TA|Setting up PEVtools}}  
# {{TA|PEVtools}}
#{{stage short|25%|February 19, 2008}}''{{TL|Finding Missing Dependencies}}''
#{{stage short|75%|February 19, 2008}}''{{TL|Fixing Broken Assets}}&mdash;tutorials, 
#:*{{stage short|75%|February 19, 2008}}''[[Trainz/AM&C/Fixing Assets|List of Faults errors and warnings messages]] &mdash; and remedies to fix such!'' 
#*{{stage short|50%|February 19, 2008}}''{{TL|Converting steam locos to run in TC3}}'' - Converting steam locos to run in TC3. If you acquire an older Locomotive with errors asset, this cookbook will help you convert the data model changed between {{TL|TC1&2}} and {{TL|TC3)) and in use {{TL|TS09}}&mdash;{{TL|TS12}}

